ists’ rejection of democracy. It focuses its analysis on two streams of Islamism: the two Islamist groups that seek “extra-parliamentary” means to achieve their goals, that is, MMI and HTI, and the PKS Islamists who choose the existing political party system as a means of their power struggle. As this book has demonstrated, there are times when the two streams of Islamism share a common platform of understanding and interpretation as well as an intersection where they are in conflict with one another. The interplay between contested meanings over particular theological matters on normative grounds and power contests among the Islamists proves to be critical in shaping this complexity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aDemocracyxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aDemocracyzIndonesia. 0aDemocracy--Indonesia. 0aDemocracy--Religious aspects--Islam. 0aIslam and politicszIndonesia. 0aIslam and politics--Indonesia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology of Religion.2bisacsh1 aHilmy, Masdar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102470708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066300608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z97831106066830 cprintz978981230971640uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981230973040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789812309730423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789812309730/original  a978-3-11-060668-3  ISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  a978-3-11-